(541, 1, '2018-01-24 06:17:30', '2018-01-24 06:17:30', 'There’s nothing as volatile as the Smartphone market. Before you start getting used to you shiny new device, there’s already a better one making news. Popular studies reveal that at the current rate, the average life-span of a new Smartphone model has reduced to under a year! So as an everyday user, by the time you finish researching on the Internet and scout thousands of reviews to finally decide on a model that you like and are excited to invest in, a new one is already announced.\r\n\r\nWell, we have some relief planned for you. If you’re planning to buy a Smartphone in 2018, you should most definitely consider our picks for the top 10 budget friendly UK Smartphones 2018. Keep your mind and eyes open for these specific models and you should end up with a pretty decent deal.\r\n\r\n<strong>Before you pick a model</strong>\r\n\r\nDecide on the OS! We don’t really need to remind you of one of the most critical Smartphone buying decisions – narrowing down the OS (Android / iOS / Windows). Make sure you know which OS you’d feel comfortable with. Also, keep your budget in mind when going through our list of the top 10 budget friendly UK Smartphones 2018. There are going to be some phones you will absolutely love regardless of their price tag, so stay focused. Or you could just give in to temptation and pick your favorite and worry about the pocket later!\r\n\r\n<strong>Let’s do this</strong>\r\n\r\nHere are the best 2018 Smartphones for the UK market expected to be priced under £300:\r\n<h5><strong>1. Samsung Galaxy S9</strong></h5>\r\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-493 size-full" src="http://pcgarage.uk.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/samsung-galaxy-s9.jpg" alt="Samsung Galaxy S9" width="610" height="253" />\r\n\r\nThe Samsung Galaxy S9 is going to be the biggest surprise of 2018. Expected to go on sale in February 2018, this Qualcomm Snapdragon powered, 6GB RAM, 64GB internal storage, 5.8in (2960x1440, 570ppi, 18.5:9) Super AMOLED display, and 12MP camera phone is expected to be priced at an unbelievably low rate of £249. At this price, if the phone makes off-the-chart pre-bookings, it won’t be a surprise.\r\n<h5><strong>2. Nokia 2</strong></h5>\r\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-494 size-full" src="http://pcgarage.uk.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Nokia-2.jpg" alt="Nokia 2" width="625" height="350" />\r\n\r\nNokia’s new budget phone, the Nokia 2, was announced in October 2017 and is expected to go on sale in the UK in 2018. The specifications of this model aren’t expected to be especially appealing – 8GB of internal storage (extendible up to 128GB), 1GB RAM, measurements of 143.5x71.3x9.30mm, 4,100mAh battery, and Qualcomm Snapdragon processor. But then, at the budget of £99, this would probably be the most decently designed budget Smartphone of 2018 and that too, from a manufacturer as reliable as Nokia.\r\n<h5>3. Nokia 7</h5>\r\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-495 size-full" src="http://pcgarage.uk.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Nokia-7.jpg" alt="Nokia 7" width="559" height="349" />\r\n\r\nThe 5th Nokia model launched in 2017, Nokia 7 is expected to be released in the UK in 2018. While the phone has already been released in China in October 2017, the worldwide release is expected to start from early 2018 and that’s when the UK market will also be getting its copy. The model has been release with some decent specifications – 5.2 inch full-HD (1920x1080, 423ppi) IPS display with Gorilla Glass, Qualcomm Snapdragon 630 processor, 4GB/6GB LPDDR4 RAM, 64GB/128GB storage, microSD extendible up to 128GB. Going by the current price at which it is launched in China, the 64GB model of the Nokia 7 will be priced at £286 in the UK.\r\n<h5><strong>4. New HTC Model</strong></h5>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="alignnone wp-image-496 size-full" src="http://pcgarage.uk.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/New-HTC-Model.jpg" alt="New HTC Model" width="700" height="402" /></p>\r\nThough HTC hasn’t announced any specific model specifications to be released in 2018, the company has gone on record to say that they will “definitely be releasing a dual-camera phone in 2018”. In fact, rumours in the industry suggest that HTC plans on releasing up to six new phones in 2018. The brand name of HTC speaks for itself and we can expect some sleek new phone to come our way, and going by the pocket-friendly range that HTC usually targets, we can expect the new models to be within the reach of most consumers.\r\n<h5>5. H<strong>onor 7X</strong></h5>\r\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-498 size-full" src="http://pcgarage.uk.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Honor-7X.jpg" alt="Honor 7X" width="700" height="402" />\r\n\r\nExpected to go on sale in early 2018, the Honor 7X model will boast of killer specifications – 5.93 inch screen with an aspect ratio of 18:9 and a resolution of 2160x1080, IPS display, 16MP back camera, 3340mAh battery, 64GB of internal storage, and dual-SIM support. Powered by a HiSilicon Kirin 659 octa-core processor and priced at £269.99, this is going to be a sweet buy.\r\n<h4><strong>6. Successors from small players who launched budget models in 2017</strong></h4>\r\nApart from the above mentioned brand names, there are a lot of small players in the market (Elephone, UMIDIGI, Wileyfox, etc.) who came up with very decent Smartphones in 2017. Their phones were priced well under the £300 and were released with good specs. So you should be on the lookout for successors of the models they launched in 2017.\r\n\r\nWhile those were the best buys under £300, if you’re okay with putting in a little more into your next purchase, here are the best UK Smartphones 2018 within the price range £300 - £500.\r\n<h4>7. M<strong>otorola Moto X4</strong></h4>\r\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-499 size-full" src="http://pcgarage.uk.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Motorola-Moto-X4.jpg" alt="Motorola Moto X4" width="700" height="402" />\r\n\r\nShowcased at IFA 2017 in Berlin, the Moto X4 is expected to hit the UK market in early 2018. The phone’s expected specifications include a 5.2 inch Full HD display, a dual-camera (12- and 8-megapixel), a front 16-megapixel camera, Snapdragon 630 processor with 3GB of RAM and 32GB of internal storage that can be expanded through a microSD card slot. This phone will cost you somewhere around £380.\r\n<h4><strong>8. LG G7</strong></h4>\r\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-502 size-full" src="http://pcgarage.uk.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/LG-G7.jpg" alt="LG G7" width="750" height="422" />\r\n\r\nThe G7 model from Korean manufacture LG is expected to be unveiled officially in January 2018 at CES. Expected to be release in February 2018, this Snapdragon powered model with an octa-core Kryo 385 CPU (four 2.8GHz high-power cores and four 1.8GHz low power cores), OLED display, and dual-camera setup is supposed to be priced at £649. However, considering that the LG G6 originally launched at £650 is now being sold at around £370, you can expect the final price of this phone to land somewhere close to £400.\r\n<h4><strong>9. OnePlus 6</strong></h4>\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-503 aligncenter" src="http://pcgarage.uk.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/OnePlus-6.jpg" alt="OnePlus 6" width="750" height="352" />\r\n\r\nDespite the recent release of OnePlus 5T, the OnePlus 6 is already being designed and is expected to be released in UK sometime around June 2018. Expected to be priced at £449, this phone will include specs similar to the 5T including the Snapdragon 845 platform, and a top-notch dual lens camera. This one is going to be a great grab!\r\n<h4>10. S<strong>ony XPeria X2</strong></h4>\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-504 aligncenter" src="http://pcgarage.uk.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Sony-XPeria-X2.jpg" alt="Sony XPeria X2" width="720" height="346" />\r\n\r\nWhile it was expected to be launched in late 2017, the Xperia X2 from Sony hasn’t been launched yet which makes its tentative release date fall sometime in 2018. Suspected to cost around £450 for the SIM free model, the phone is rumoured to have the Snapdragon 820, or maybe the slightly lower 810 processor, fingerprint sensor, 4GB RAM, and a USB-C port.\r\n\r\n<strong>Wrapping it up</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you’re setting out to buy a budget friendly Smartphone in 2018, your choices are pretty good. So unless you want to take the plunge only to regret it a few months later, do give our list above some serious thought.', 'Top 10 Budget Friendly UK Smartphones to buy in 2018', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '439-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-01-24 06:17:30', '2018-01-24 06:17:30', '', 439, 'http://pcgarage.uk.com/blog/439-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
